<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Bar 1: Dm 2nd inversion in RH (A-D), open LH (D2-A2-F3) — light opening
- Bar 2: vi substituted for V/ii (A7→Am) — diatonic constraint
- Bar 3: Dm 1st inversion in LH for bass variety (F2 bass)
- Bar 4: Am with 4-note close voicing build (A-C-E-A)
- Bar 5: Climax — Am7 full 4-voice open (A-E-G-C), F with doubled root
- Bar 6: C major with added 9th texture; V→I arc
- Bar 7: Dm7 voicing (D-A-C-F) for added richness before final
- Bar 8: viiø7 (E-Bb-D-G) half-dim passing chord, resolves to Dm close

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Inner voice Bb (LH top) steps down to A (bar 1→2) between Gm→Am
- C5 sustained across bar 6 measures (RH common tone F→C)
- Final Eø7→Dm: E→D stepwise in bass, G→F stepwise in inner voice

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-2: 2-3 harp voices, sparse opening (grief/sorrow character)
- Bars 3-4: 3-voice buildup, inversions add harmonic interest
- Bars 5-6: Full 4+2 voicing (LH 4-note, RH 2-note) at melodic peak
- Bars 7-8: 4+2 sustained then convergence to close root-pos Dm
-->
